channel.title: What's wrong
channel.description:
My friend tried starting his fr33sc4p3 server and got this...
[code]Starting fr33sc4p3 Server on 0.0.0.0:43594 Error Download File[/code]
Anyone know what's wrong?

item.title: What's wrong
item.dc:creator: @PatScape PatScape
item.description:
@PatScape wrote:

Yes, that’s true, but whenever my client glitches, It shows in my runserver.bat. A cache is a data storage, or any kind of storage. In the case of private servers it holds all of the hard-coded data such as item names, npc names, and the global map.

Read full topic

item.title: What's wrong
item.dc:creator: @mrdek11 mrdek11
item.description:
@mrdek11 wrote:

I think you’re following me, as I’ve been answering all the posts for a while :p.
Also, he said his friend started a server, and he got the error, not a client, So unless he has one of those hi-tech add-ons that require a downloaded update every once in a while, (silab uses some I think), then I have no clue what it’s downloading.[br][size=1]Posted on: June 09, 2007, 10:49:31 PM[/size][hr]The cache is the game data, that holds all the graphics etc.
From the code you posted at the top (the error) it was a server that got the error, seeing as it says “starting server at 0.0.0.0:43594”
